sql:
SELECT AVG(mother_bmi) AS average_bmi_non_smoking_employed_mothers
FROM mothers
WHERE mother_smoking_status = 0 AND mother_employment_status = 'Employed';

external_knowledge:
A live birth is the birth of an infant with any signs of life after being expelled or extracted from the mother's body.; 
BMI is calculated as weight (in kg) divided by height (in meters) squared and is an indicator of body fatness.; 
Gestation weeks refer to the number of weeks the mother was pregnant.
